# Angular2 Starter

>An Angular2 starter kit featuring [Angular 2](https://angular.io/) (Router, Http, Forms, Services, Tests, E2E, Coverage), [Karma](https://karma-runner.github.io/1.0/index.html), [Protractor](https://www.protractortest.org/#/), [Jasmine](https://jasmine.github.io/), [Istanbul](https://istanbul.js.org/), [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/index.html), and [Webpack](https://webpack.js.org/).

 </p>
 
## Getting Started

* Run: `npm install` to install all the necessary dependencies.
* Run:`npm run server` to get up and running instance.
* Follow the Complete Directory Layout to get to know about the project.

### Complete Directory Layout


```
 /config/                     # 
 /doc/                        # Documentation files for the project
 /node_modules/               # 3rd-party libraries and utilities
 /src/                        # Contain the source of the starter kit
    /app/                    # Contain app specific code base(.ts, .html and .scss) of the project
       /core/               # Core code base of the application 
          /components/     # Contain all the components(files or folders)
          /directives/     # Contain all the directives(files or folders)
          /models/         # Contain all data models(files or folders)
          /pipes/          # 
          /providers/      # Contain all the providers(files or folders)
          /core.module.ts  # 
          /index.ts/       #
       /index.ts/           # 
    /assets/                 # Contain all the assests(image files or icons)
    /meta/                   # Contains all the meta configurations for the project
    /styles/                 # Contain all the styles(files or folders)
 .editorconfig                # Define and maintain consistent coding styles between different editors and IDEs
 .gitattributes               # Defining attributes per path
 .gitignore                   # Contains files to be ignored when pushing to git
 .nvmrc                       # 
 .travis.yml                  # 
 Dockerfile                   # 
 firebase.json                # 
 karma.conf.js                # Test runner in .ts format
 LICENSE                      # Contains License Agreement file
 netlify.toml                 # 
 package.json                 # Holds various metadata relevant to the project
 protractor.conf.js           # 
 README.md                    # Contains all the details of the project
 tsconfig.json                # Contains typescript compiler options
 tsconfig.webpack.json        # 
 tslint.json                  # Lint rules for the project
 typedoc.json                 # 
 webpack.config.js            # 
```

## Technologies

Usage          	            | Technology
--------------------------	| --------------------------
Javascript Framework        | Typescript, Angular
Unit Testing Framework     	| Jasmine
Unit Test Runner           	| Karma
Coverage Generator         	| Istanbul
Documentation              	| Typedoc
Task Running Tool           | Gulp 
Build Tool                	| Webpack
Code Quality Tools         	| JS Hint, TS Lint
Dependency Registries      	| Bower, NPM

## How to use

Here is the list of tasks available out of the box and run these via `npm run <task>`
```
  build             Perform npm and bower build
  clean             Cleans src directory
  test              Run spec tests
  dev-test          Runs the test specs with Chrome
  coverage          Generate coverage reports by running all the tests via karma
  doc               Generate API Documentation
  tsconfig-update   Update files section in tsconfig.json using filesGlob entries
  watch             Watches ts source files and runs tslint, jshint on change
  patch             Update patch version and create tag
  feature           Update feature version and create tag
  release           Update release version and create tag
```
